exercises.problem_statement:
Define:

typedef struct {
    char name[50];
    int emp_id;
    float salary;
} Employee;

Read n employees. Compute and print the average salary and the name of the highest-paid employee.

Define:

typedef struct {
    char name[50];
    int quantity;
    float price;
} Product;

Read n products. Implement: search by product name (print details if found, 'Not found' otherwise), sort by price (ascending) using bubble sort on structs, and display the sorted list.

Define:

typedef struct Node {
    int data;
    struct Node *next;
} Node;

Write functions to: create a node (malloc + data + next=NULL), append a node to the end of the list, traverse and print all nodes, and free all nodes. Build a list from N user-supplied integers and print it.
